<h1>About Raise your Voice</h1>
 <br>
<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow"><b>What is Raise Your Voice?</b></font></p>
 <br>
<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow"><b>Raise Your Voice</b> is a 24-hour 
karaoke marathon to benefit <b>Ethos Music Center</b> held at Voicebox 
Karaoke, located on 21<sup>st</sup> and NW Hoyt. If you like karaoke, 
put your money where your mic is on <b>September 24</b><sup><b>th</b></sup><b> 

and 25</b><sup><b>th</b></sup><b> 2009, </b>
and join hundreds of fellow singers to keep the music going all night 
long…and then some! Help provide music education to thousands of students 
across Oregon by raising your voice! Raise Your Voice is the first fundraiser 
of this kind to be held in the Portland area. </font></p>
 <br> <br>
<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow"><b>When will Raise Your Voice 
take place?</b></font></p>
 <br>
<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow">This fundraiser will take place <b>
September 24</b><sup><b>th</b></sup><b> 

– 25</b><sup><b>th</b></sup>. The event will begin on Thursday, September 
24<sup>th</sup> with a kickoff event from 4pm-5pm. Kids from Ethos Music 
Center will start the night with a talent performance. The karaoke will 
begin at 5pm and teams will be singing non-stop until 5pm on Friday, 
September 25<sup>th</sup>.  Teams sign up for a portion of the 
24-hours, so the building will be rocking all night long. Of course, 
teams are welcome to step up to the challenge and sing for all 24 hours!  
Throughout the event, we will provide entertainment (vendor booths, 
bands, movies, etc.) to make Raise Your Voice an exciting experience 
for all participants throughout the duration of the event. </font></p>
 <br>
<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow"><b>How does it work?</b></font></p>
 <br> <br>
<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow"><b>It’s pretty easy. </b>

Team Captains start teams and get their friends to join. Captains tell 
us when the team wants to sing and each team signs up for at least 3 
hours work of singing time. Teams commit to raising at least $500 per 
hour of singing (3 hours = $1,500 goal). Six teams can sing at once. 
A team can sign up for as many hours as the wish, but must commit to 
the <i>minimum of</i> <i>$500 per hour for three hours</i>. Teams of 
various sizes are welcome to register, including teams of one. We will 
do our best to schedule teams based on their time preferences.  
We will notify teams <i>at least two weeks prior</i> to the event.</font></p>
 <br>
<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow">Once the team is formed, <b>friends 
can join</b> and ask their friends to help <b>sponsor their teams</b>. 
All donations are collected and tracked on this site in real time, so 
everyone can see where they stand. Prizes are awarded to those who raise 
the most – teams and individuals. </font></p>

 <br>
<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow">Then, on September 24<sup>th</sup>, 
we will celebrate our hard work and <b>raise our voices</b> for Ethos 
and the importance of music education. </font></p>
 <br>
<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow">If the minimum amount is raised 
for all timeslots, we will raise <b>$72,000</b>. We anticipate teams 
exceeding this goal!</font></p>
