<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow"><b>What is Ethos Music Center?</b></font></p>
 <br>
<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow"><b>Ethos Music Center </b>
is dedicated to the promotion of music and music based education for 
youth in underserved communities. Ethos serves over 7,000 students a 
year throughout the state of Oregon with direct and sustained music 
education.  Ethos firmly believes that music education and its 
associated academic benefits keep at-risk children engaged in their 
families, their communities, and their futures.          </font></p>
 <br>
<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow">Ethos is dedicated to continuing 
a tradition of quality programming and organizational sustainability. 
Ethos Music Center has a comprehensive fundraising strategy comprised 
of major gifts, membership, annual appeals, fundraising events, and 
corporate and foundation support. Ethos also generates over 60% of earned 
revenue income through fees-for-services and the operation of the Ethos 
Café.</font></p>
<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow">  </font></p>
<p><font size="3" face="Arial Narrow">Ethos Music Center maintains a 
low administrative cost of only 11% (most nonprofit organizations operate 
at 18-22%) so financial gifts go directly towards bringing music education 
to the lives of Oregon’s school aged children. </font></p>

